2 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
3 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
4 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 567.4c of Title 59, unless there
5 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
6 A. An Advanced Practice Registered Nurse recognized by the
7 Oklahoma Board of Nursing as a Certified Nurse Practitioner,
8 Clinical Nurse Specialist, or Certified Nurse-Midwife who has
9 completed a minimum of six thousand two hundred forty (6,240)
10 clinical practice hours with prescriptive authority supervised by a
11 physician may apply to the Oklahoma Board of Nursing for authority
12 to prescribe and order independent of supervision.
13 B. The application for independent prescriptive authority shall
14 include proof that the Certified Nurse Practitioner, Clinical Nurse
15 Specialist, or Certified Nurse-Midwife:
16 1. Holds a valid, current license in the appropriate Advanced
17 Practice Registered Nurse role issued by the Board and is in good
18 standing with the Board; and
19 2. Has completed a minimum of six thousand two hundred forty
20 (6,240) clinical practice hours with prescriptive authority
21 supervised by a physician. This paragraph shall not be construed to
22 exclude practice hours with supervised prescriptive authority
23 obtained prior to the effective date of this act from being counted
24 toward the hours required in this paragraph.
ENGR. S. A. TO ENGR. H. B. NO. 2298 Page 3

1 C. Independent prescriptive authority granted under this
2 section shall be valid until the expiration of the current license
3 to practice and may be renewed upon application to the Board at the
4 same time and for the same period as the renewal of the license to
5 practice.
6 D. The Board may suspend or revoke independent prescriptive
7 authority granted under this section in accordance with the
8 Administrative Procedures Act for violation of the provisions of, or
9 the rules promulgated under, the Oklahoma Nursing Practice Act.
10 E. The Board may assess a reasonable fee for the review of
11 initial and renewal applications under the provisions of this
12 section.
13 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
14 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 567.5b of Title 59, unless there
15 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
16 A. An Advanced Practice Registered Nurse, or the employer of
17 the Advanced Practice Registered Nurse on his or her behalf, shall
18 carry malpractice insurance or demonstrate proof of financial
19 responsibility in a minimum amount of One Million Dollars
20 ($1,000,000.00) per occurrence and Three Million Dollars
21 ($3,000,000.00) in the aggregate per year. This requirement shall
22 apply only to the Advanced Practice Registered Nurse and shall not
23 be construed as to require the Advanced Practice Registered Nurse to
24 provide malpractice insurance coverage to any supervising physician.
